---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Gas-phase Metallicity - ArXiv Atlas";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Gas-phase Metallicity</h1>

    <p>
      Gas-phase metallicity (12+log(O/H)) is an observational tracer of a galaxy's chemical enrichment. In Karthikeyan et al. (2026) it is estimated from strong-line ratios using AURORA high-z calibrations and used to test correlations with nebular and stellar reddening (Section II.3.2; Section III.3). [Section II.3.2; Section III.3]
    </p>

    <h2 id="measurement">Measurement</h2>
    <p>Strong-line ratios such as [OIII]/Hβ, [OIII]/[OII], and [NeIII]/[OII] are combined with calibrations to infer 12+log(O/H); uncertainties are estimated via Monte Carlo perturbation (Karthikeyan et al. 2026, Section II.3.2). [Section II.3.2]</p>

    <h2 id="see-also">See also</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/nebular_reddening" text="Nebular Reddening" /></li>
      <li><WikiLink slug="pages/balmer_decrement" text="Balmer Decrement" /></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="references">
      <h2>References</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Karthikeyan, S., Clarke, L., Shapley, A. E., et al. (2026). "Balmer Decrements and Nebular-Stellar Reddening in JADES Galaxies at 2.7&lt;z&lt;7." arXiv:2603.11338. <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11338">https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11338</a> (Section II.3.2; Section III.3).</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
